The paper deals with image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of unsupervised output embeddings derived from text corpora suggests a potential overlap with natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The learning of a compatibility function also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
